'''Varun Dhawan''' ({{IPA-hi|ʋəˈrʊɳ dʱəˈʋən|}}; born 24 April 1987) is an Indian actor. One of the country's highest-paid celebrities, he has featured in ''[[Forbes India]]''{{'s}} [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] list since 2014. Several of the films in which he starred were commercially successful, establishing Dhawan in [[Bollywood|Hindi cinema]].

Born to the film director [[David Dhawan]], he studied business management from the [[Nottingham Trent University]], after which he worked as an assistant director to [[Karan Johar]] on the 2010 drama ''[[My Name Is Khan]]''. He made his acting debut in 2012 in Johar's teen drama ''[[Student of the Year]]''. He rose to prominence with starring roles in the romantic comedies ''[[Main Tera Hero]]'' (2014), ''[[Humpty Sharma Ki Dulhania]]'' (2014), and ''[[Badrinath Ki Dulhania]]'' (2017); the action comedies ''[[Dilwale (2015 film)|Dilwale]]'' (2015), ''[[Dishoom]]'' (2016), and ''[[Judwaa 2]]'' (2017); the dance film ''[[ABCD 2]]'' (2015); and the drama ''[[Sui Dhaaga]]'' (2018). He also received praise for playing an avenger in the crime thriller ''[[Badlapur (film)|Badlapur]]'' (2015) and an aimless man coping with loss in the drama ''[[October (2018 film)|October]]'' (2018).

